snippet.title: Parenting Social Media - DTNS 4235
snippet.description:
Do social media companies have a responsibility to their for social ills that might come about from the use of their services? If so, what's the threshold of responsibility? FIDO the authentication alliance dedicated to replacing passwords believes it has found the way to break through user hesitation on ditching passwords. And gadget blogs and tech news sites are gushing over Apple’s Universal Control feature.

Starring Tom Merritt, Sarah Lane, Stephanie Humphrey, Roger Chang, Joe.

snippet.title: Modern Software Engineering • Dave Farley & Steve Smith • GOTO 2022
snippet.description:
This interview was recorded for the GOTO Book Club. #GOTOcon #GOTObookclub
http://gotopia.tech/bookclub

Dave Farley - Author of "Modern Software Engineering", Continuous Delivery & DevOps Pioneer
Steve Smith - Author of "Measuring Continuous Delivery", Principal Consultant at Equal Experts

Find plenty more from Dave on his Continuous Delivery YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCCfqyGl3nq_V0bo64CjZh8g

DESCRIPTION
What should the modern software engineer know in order to be the best at their job? Dave Farley and Steve Smith explore the books that can help engineers succeed and why iteration and experiments are crucial. The discussion is centered around Dave’s latest book “Modern Software Engineering.”
The interview is based on Dave's book "Modern Software Engineering": https://amzn.to/3GI468M

TIMECODES
00:00 Intro
01:45 Software engineering books that shook our foundation
06:36 Modern software engineering in practice
09:52 Working iteratively
18:33 The experimental software engineer
29:09 Managing complexity in the cloud age
40:16 How to apply the separation of concerns in a team
46:28 Rolling the wheel of time
53:15 What’s next after Modern Software Engineering?
01:03:52 Outro

Read the full transcription of the interview here:
https://gotopia.tech/bookclub/episodes/modern-software-engineering

snippet.title: Winning A Dev.Post Hackathon - Tiles@MapHub, OpenStreetMap with Dustin Wilson | HackBuddy
snippet.description:
Presented by HackBuddy, a meetup group from Southern California that learns web programming together now ONLINE.  Join us from around the world, simply get on the mailing list via: https://javascriptla.net.    

Tiles@Maphub allows users to query through hundreds of GB of OpenStreetMap (OSM) data and dynamically construct custom vector layers from this data. Tiles relies on a PostGIS DB tuned for fast geospatial queries on the newest generation of AWS Graviton processors. Tiles was built using AWS ECS as a container orchestrator, PostGIS as the DB, Redis as an API cache, Go for APIs, and vanilla Javascript for the frontend.

Dustin Wilson is a backend engineer at Numina, a start-up that deploys remote sensors to measure how people and objects move in streets and public spaces. Wilson also contributes content to Codecademy, where he focuses on building content for Databases and Computer Science courses (e.g. DB Design with PostgreSQL, CS103: Databases). Before Numina, Wilson was a Data Engineer at Geophy, a Dutch real-estate tech company. Dustin has a B.A in Economics from Columbia University.

Enjoy the video! Thumbs up if you liked, leave comments below and SUBSCRIBE if you're new!  See you at the next meetup. Visit our website at:  https://javascriptla.net for more meetup and event announcements!
